-- Goldman Sachs Raises Iron Ore Forecast by 4% for 2011, Coking Coal by 6%
-- B y   E l i s a b e t h   B e h r m a n n
-- 2010-11-30T23:52:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-30/goldman-sachs-raises-iron-ore-forecast-by-4-for-2011-coking-coal-by-6-.html
Goldman Sachs & Partners Australia
Pty. increased its forcast for the price of hard coking coal,
used in steelmaking, by 6 percent to $240 a metric ton for next
year because of growing demand from China, India and Brazil.
Goldman also boosted its iron ore price forecast for 2011,
raising it to $153 a ton, up 4 percent. The three-year average
price for iron ore was revised up 22 percent, the bank said in a
note dated Nov. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
